Galaxy Watch5 features body composition analysis, improved sensors that get an accurate read on your heart rate and Advanced Sleep Coaching that helps you get your zzzs .       4.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Good watch with some software issues.
      Reviewed in the United States on September 16, 2023
      Color: Gray Titanium
      It's a good watch, but there are some disappointing experiences: 1) First time I went for a run and wanted to test out the cellular connection, it overheated and told me to wait. This happened twice since I've owned the watch, and it's usually been... See more
      It's a good watch, but there are some disappointing experiences:

      1) First time I went for a run and wanted to test out the cellular connection, it overheated and told me to wait. This happened twice since I've owned the watch, and it's usually been on actually hot days. I do have a protective cover, so that may be part o the problem.

      2) Run tracking is buggy...sometimes. I often start my run from my front door, where my watch has a connection with either my WiFi or phone. When I start a run from this location, it always seems to have trouble determining how far I've run. I'll be 3 minutes into my run and it will say I've done a mile (I wish!). If I bring my phone with me, there is no issue. If I drive to a trail and run it does perfectly fine. I have the feeling their run tracking is using a WiFi rough location to start my run.

      3) Spotify. This won't count against the watch so much, because it's probably mostly a software issue. I would think it's a pretty good chance that using Spotify with headphones while you're not around your phone is a pretty good use case for a cellular watch. This does work, but it's really not intuitive to use. Sometimes the Spotify UI will just sit there and not tell you whether it's trying to play something, or if it's loading, or whatever. You can literally sit there for minutes fiddling around trying to figure out what Spotify is trying to do. Sometimes when it does work, the events are delayed. For instance I may have chosen a song 10 seconds ago, and gotten no feedback from the UI, yet it will eventually play something.

      4) Google's apps aren't fully integrated. It's like they're still not fully committed to wearables. For instance, if someone is at the door, you will get a notification. Would you like to see who it is? Well, you will have to go find your phone. There are many apps that don't show useful notifications on the watch. There is so much opportunity to make wearables actually much better than they are, and it's frustrating that Google just doesn't put in the effort.

      That's pretty much the bad stuff. Now for the good news. When this watch works, it does a really nice job. The watch faces built in are really nice IMO, and you can customize them pretty well with useful shortcuts. (I added a shortcut to start a workout and another to set a timer). We do get Google Assistant now, and I've assigned mine to be triggered by long pressing one of the buttons. Google pay works fine for me. In my experience the battery is much much better than my previous Android watches, which removes some level of anxiety. The build quality is great. I am rough with my watches, and the screen on this one is pretty much scratch free at this point. I take this in the pool and in the shower, so absolutely no issues with water exposure. The workout tracking software is actually great when it is recording correctly.

      I originally had a Galaxy Watch 4 Classic 42mm Bluetooth/LTE from Best Buy that was an open box for over $300 at the time. I happened to be looking for a smartwatch for my girlfriend when I came across this amazon renewed Galaxy Watch 5 Pro for a fraction of the price (under $100). For that price, I decided to get it. The condition was described as excellent. I guess theres one higher rated condition they label as pristine. I was a little skeptical, but when I got it, I was really impressed. It looked as if it was refurbished to new condition. There were no signs of scratches or wear. I put a screen protector on, charged it, powered it on and went through the setup process using a backup of my other watch. It transfered most of my settings and data over but I had to tweak the layout of my tiles and watch face to make it the familiar look and feel of my old watch. The charger that came with it is a 3rd party unfortunately, but I have an OEM Samsung charger so that doesn't bother me too much. I do suggest you spend the extra money to get an official charger or for a few bucks more, a quick charger as I have not found a 3rd party charger that charges as fast as a Samsung one. Also note that during the setup, you will drain quite a bit of battery. I went through about 40% during my setup. After I went to bed and woke up with still having a significant amount of battery life. With some proper settings, you can expect to see a full day or 2 before charging it. This watch is a little heavier than my old one, but is also a little bigger and has a larger battery, so that's expected. I smacked my old watch on many things and expect this watch to be just as durable, especially with the thick frame it has. It connected to my phone seamlessly and was able to disconnect and reconnect without any issues. I tested the speaker, screen, microphone, buttons, Bluetooth connection, and charging without any issues. I didn't test the water resistance. I did purchase a 3 year wearable protection plan for this watch just in case something were to happen, but the durability of these watches, I don't expect to ever use it. Hope this review helps you.

      Also I'll add that the included charger was some knockoff Walmart special! The band was one of those 3$ Chinese elastic straps that you can get 3+ for 5$ on Amazon that are horrible looking. Thankfully I had a few bands i bought with my other watch that I used to test..

      Their sending me a replacement and I'll report back if the replacement is indeed up to par or if it's getting sent back as well for a full refund and I'll just have to buy another new watch!

      Edit--also just noticed that this is NOT Amazon renewed selling this watch which i wish I would of caught sooner, it's somebody named "ChubbiesTech"... and upon closer look their reviews are absolutely horrible so I have a feeling the replacement watch will be going back also!
